"Isn't there any heating?"[p]
Lisa's eyes shifted to the heater in the back of the room.[p]
"I'm sorry.[p]
This worked until yesterday, but today it's broken.[p]
It's ironic."[p]
Lisa shrugged her shoulders.[p]
"But there should be an oil heater for use in the patient rooms in the reception area...[p]
I will go and get it."[p]
Lisa begins to stand but I stop her.[p]
"I will go and get it. [p]
You just sit tight."[p]
Lisa smiled.[p]
"You are kind."[p]
I pretended not to hear her as I left the room.[p]


